President Muhammadu Buhari, on Friday, greeted the Governor of Benue State, Samuel Ortom on his 60th birthday. A statement by presidential spokesman, Garba Shehu, conveyed Buhari’s message. It said the President joined family and friends to celebrate the Governor and thank God for a life of service to his state and the nation. As the former minister marks the Diamond Jubilee, Buhari urged him to “rededicate his life to working for the prosperity and well-being of the people of Benue State.” The Nigerian leader wished Ortom many more years in good health.